A Blockchain enthusiast, Olom Godspower Jones, has highlighted risks associated with trading in digital assets. He noted that while the digital crypto market is now worth over $400 billion and has a trading volume of about $39 billion, it was important to understand the threats before venturing into it. In a chat with The Nation, he said: “Investing in the high volatile cryptocurrency market is a risky undertaking and one needs to learn about proper risk management before venturing in. “New traders/investors who want to venture into cryptocurrency need to understand what cryptocurrency and the technology behind it are all about.   ‘What Edevbie will bring to Delta as governor’     Fed Govt promises early repair of burnt Apongbon bridge     ‘Tackle insecurity to protect women, children’   “Some of the problems facing cryptocurrencies today are cyber theft, high volatility, as well as a lack of clear regulation/government interference. “New traders need to be less greedy and knowledgeable about the use of various technical analysis tools. “Every new trader needs to invest only what they can afford to lose as there is no guarantee of minimum profitability or break-even on investments. “Trading in cryptos has a high volatility rate and not perfect for traders because it generates high levels of uncertainty, coupled with the bias that it gives crypto traders less time to react.”